re, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Feurs, Loire, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France","Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Wondrous’ or ‘enlightenment’.","2  ♀ ‘Fine jade’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert II de Courcelles-du-Breuil was born in 1225, in Le Breuil, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France, his father, Amaury DE COURCELLES-DE-BREUIL, was 26 and his mother, Maragde DE VICHY, was 25. He married Philippa de Baffie about 1240. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died about 1276, in Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1225–about 1276":"1225–umbes 1276","1225–1276":"1225–1276","1222–1264":"1222–1264","1245–1263":"1245–1263","1200–1250":"1200–1250","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","environ 1245":"umbes 1245","environ 1263":"umbes 1263","environ 1240":"umbes 1240","avant 1264":"enne 1264","environ 1250":"umbes 1250","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","1225":"1225","1245":"1245","1200":"1200","1222":"1222","1276":"1276","about 1276":"umbes 1276","Le Breuil, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Le Breuil, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Le Breuil, Rhône, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Le Breuil, Rhône, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Feurs, Loire, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Feurs, Loire, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1225–about 1276":"1225–noin 1276","1225–1276":"1225–1276","1222–1264":"1222–1264","1245–1263":"1245–1263","1200–1250":"1200–1250","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","environ 1245":"noin 1245","environ 1263":"noin 1263","environ 1240":"noin 1240","avant 1264":"ennen vuotta 1264","environ 1250":"noin 1250","1264":"1264","1263":"1263","1250":"1250","1225":"1225","1245":"1245","1200":"1200","1222":"1222","1276":"1276","about 1276":"noin 1276","Le Breuil, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Le Breuil, Allier, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Ranska","Le Breuil, Rhône, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Le Breuil, Rhône, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Ranska","Feurs, Loire, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Fran